snippet: Missouri Gov.-elect Eric Greitens said Monday he opposes taxpayer money to help build a new soccer stadium in St. Louis, calling the project "nothing more than welfare for millionaires."...
lead_paragraph: Missouri Gov.-elect Eric Greitens said Monday he opposes taxpayer money to help build a new soccer stadium in St. Louis, calling the project "nothing more than welfare for millionaires."

headline.main: Incoming Governor Opposes St. Louis Soccer Stadium Funding
headline.print_headline: Incoming Governor Opposes St. Louis Soccer Stadium Funding
